comment:
* Result sent back from the UI after the user chose an option and completed the following
 * transaction launched through the provider PendingIntent associated with that option.
 *
 * @hide

methods.name: public static void sendUserSelectionResult(@NonNull ResultReceiver resultReceiver, @NonNull UserSelectionResult userSelectionResult)
methods.comment:
* Sends the completed {@code userSelectionResult} back to the CredentialManager service.
     *
     * @param resultReceiver the ResultReceiver sent from the system service, that can be extracted
     *                       from the launch intent via
     *                       {@link IntentHelper#extractResultReceiver(Intent)}

methods.name: public String getProviderId()
methods.comment:
* Returns the provider identifier (component name or package name) whose entry was selected by
     * the user.

methods.name: public String getEntryKey()
methods.comment: Returns the identifier of the visual entry that the user selected.

methods.name: public String getEntrySubkey()
methods.comment: Returns the sub-identifier of the visual entry that the user selected.

methods.name: public ProviderPendingIntentResponse getPendingIntentProviderResponse()
methods.comment: Returns the pending intent response from the provider.

methodNames: public static void sendUserSelectionResult(@NonNull ResultReceiver resultReceiver, @NonNull UserSelectionResult userSelectionResult)
